This article is about Executive Order 13582, issued by President Barack Obama on August 18, 2011. The order blocks the property of the Government of Syria and prohibits certain transactions with respect to Syria. It states that all property and interests in property of the Government of Syria, as well as any person determined to have supported them, are blocked and may not be transferred, paid, exported, withdrawn, or otherwise dealt with. The order also prohibits new investment in Syria by a United States person, the exportation of services to Syria, the importation of petroleum or petroleum products of Syrian origin into the United States, and any transaction or dealing related to petroleum or petroleum products of Syrian origin. It further prohibits the making of donations to any person whose property is blocked under this order. The order applies to all United States persons and any transactions that evade or attempt to violate the prohibitions are also prohibited. The order allows for exceptions for transactions conducted for the official business of the Federal Government. The Secretary of the Treasury, in consultation with the Secretary of State, is authorized to take necessary actions to carry out the purposes of this order. The order is effective as of August 18, 2011.